    "caption_instruction": "RULE #1 — ABSENCES: Only describe what IS visible. Never write about what is NOT present.\nBANNED phrases (never write): \"no tattoos\", \"no clothing\", \"no sexual activity\", \"no BDSM\", \"no BDSM elements\", \"no bondage\", \"no restraints\", \"no explicit\", \"no piercings\", \"no penetration\", \"does not apply\", \"is not depicted\", \"none is visible\", \"cannot be confirmed\", \"no signs of\", \"are not visible\", \"are not present\", \"is not present\", \"are not depicted\", or any sentence that states, summarizes, or lists what is NOT present. Do NOT add a closing disclaimer or summary after describing the image.\nSTOP RULE: Your final sentence must describe something you can see. When all visible attributes are covered, stop writing immediately. Do NOT end with any sentence about what is absent, not present, or not depicted.\nIf something is not present, simply omit it. Do not mention it at all.\n\nVISIBILITY RULE: If the image is too dark, blurry, or heavily cropped to determine a specific detail with confidence, omit that detail entirely — never guess or approximate.\n\nWrite a thorough, factual description of this image. Cover all visible attributes completely — do not pad or repeat yourself, and do not exceed 400 words.\n\nCover each of the following that is clearly visible:\n\n- Hair: exact color (if hair appears very light or platinum, describe as \"platinum blonde\" unless roots are clearly gray), length, texture, style\n- Skin: skin tone\n- Build: slim / athletic / average / curvy / plus size\n- Breasts (if exposed): size (small / medium / large / very large), shape (perky / round / teardrop / sagging), nipple color (pink / brown / dark), nipple state (erect / soft), areola size (small / large)\n- Vulva (if exposed): grooming (shaved / trimmed / natural / hairy), labia appearance (closed / slightly open / spread / gaping)\n- Buttocks (if exposed): ALWAYS state both size (small / medium / large / very large) AND shape (flat / round / bubble butt / wide / athletic). Use those exact terms. A rear-view or buttocks-focused image MUST include a size word and a shape word — do not describe the buttocks without them. Use \"buttocks\" or \"ass\" to name this body part — do NOT write \"rear\" alone (it is ambiguous with rear-entry position).\n- Penis (if visible): erect or flaccid, circumcised or uncircumcised\n- Clothing or accessories: describe each item\n- Pose and position: body orientation, limb placement\n- Sexual activity — use ONLY these exact terms:\n  vaginal sex — STRICT RULE: ONLY use this term if BOTH are true: (1) the labia are visibly SPLIT APART by the shaft itself, AND (2) the shaft clearly enters the vaginal canal (the lower opening). Labia merely visible near the penis does NOT qualify.\n  REAR-ENTRY DEFAULT: If the receiving person faces AWAY from the camera (doggy style, bent over, from behind), you are looking at their rear. In this view the anus is the UPPER opening and the vaginal opening is the LOWER opening. Penetration occurring in a rear-entry scene MUST be described as ANAL SEX unless you can explicitly see the shaft entering the vaginal canal specifically. Labia being visible from behind does NOT mean the penis is in the vagina — they are always visible from that angle regardless of which opening is penetrated. WHEN IN DOUBT IN ANY REAR-ENTRY SCENE: USE ANAL SEX.\n  anal sex — use this term if ANY of these are true: (a) the receiving person faces away and penetration is occurring, (b) the penis enters the buttocks, anus, or rear from behind, (c) the sphincter is visible around the shaft, (d) the person is in doggy style or bent-over position with penetration. The buttocks have only ONE internal opening — the anus.\n  If penetration point is genuinely ambiguous and the couple is face-to-face — omit both terms. Never guess.\n  blowjob (mouth or tongue on penis — NEVER call this cunnilingus; hand holding penis during oral = still blowjob, not handjob)\n  deepthr