    "tag_instruction": "Read the ENTIRE description below before generating any tags. Every attribute mentioned in the description should become a tag.\n\nReturn ONLY a JSON array of strings. Work through each numbered step below in order. Add one tag per attribute that appears in the description. Skip a step only if that attribute is not mentioned.\n\n1. Hair color — 1 tag (e.g. \"blonde hair\", \"dark hair\", \"platinum blonde\")\n2. Hair length — 1 tag (e.g. \"long hair\", \"short hair\", \"medium length hair\")\n3. Hair style — 1 tag if distinct (e.g. \"curly hair\", \"wavy hair\", \"straight hair\", \"ponytail\")\n4. Skin tone — 1 tag (e.g. \"fair skin\", \"light skin\", \"medium skin\", \"dark skin\", \"tan skin\")\n5. Build — 1 tag (e.g. \"slim\", \"athletic\", \"average build\", \"curvy\", \"plus size\")\n\nANATOMY GATE — READ BEFORE STEPS 6–13:\nScan the description for these words: \"breast\", \"nipple\", \"vulva\", \"labia\", \"pussy\", \"vagina\", \"buttocks\", \"ass\", \"anus\", \"penis\", \"nude\", \"naked\", \"bare\", \"topless\", \"genitals\".\nIf NONE of these words appear in the description → SKIP steps 6 through 13 entirely. Go directly to step 14.\nIf the description says the subject is clothed or wearing clothing without mentioning exposed anatomy → SKIP steps 6 through 13 entirely. Go directly to step 14.\nOnly enter steps 6–13 if the description explicitly states that specific anatomy is exposed or visible. A clothed body part is NOT exposed — skip its step.\n\nANATOMY RULE: Every anatomy tag MUST include the body part name. Never output a bare adjective. Write \"perky breasts\" not \"perky\". Write \"shaved pussy\" not \"shaved\". Write \"round butt\" not \"round\". Each size and shape descriptor is a SEPARATE tag — do NOT merge them (e.g. \"medium breasts\" and \"perky breasts\" are two separate tags, never \"medium perky breasts\").\n\n6. Breast size — 1 tag: \"small breasts\" / \"medium breasts\" / \"large breasts\" / \"very large breasts\"\n7. Breast shape — 1 tag: \"perky breasts\" / \"round breasts\" / \"teardrop breasts\" / \"sagging breasts\"\n8. Nipple color — 1 tag: \"pink nipples\" / \"brown nipples\" / \"dark nipples\"\n   Areola — 1 tag: \"small areola\" / \"large areola\" (only if the description explicitly mentions areola size; skip if not mentioned)\n9. Nipple state — output \"erect nipples\" ONLY if the description uses any of these words to describe the nipples: \"erect\", \"hard\", \"hardened\", \"stiff\", \"protruding\", or \"pebbled\". If nipples are described as soft, or not described at all, SKIP this step entirely. Do NOT output \"soft nipples\", \"nipple state\", or any other value here.\n\n10. Vulva grooming — 1 tag: \"shaved pussy\" / \"trimmed pussy\" / \"natural pussy\" / \"hairy pussy\"\n11. Labia appearance — 1 tag: \"spread labia\" / \"open labia\" / \"gaping pussy\" (only if described as spread/open/gaping)\n\n12. Buttocks size — 1 tag: \"small butt\" / \"medium butt\" / \"large butt\" / \"very large butt\"\n    Inference: if the description mentions \"buttocks\", \"posterior\", \"butt\", or \"ass\" without an explicit size word, use context to pick the best size tag. If context gives no clue, output \"medium butt\".\n13. Buttocks shape — 1 tag: \"round butt\" / \"bubble butt\" / \"flat butt\" / \"wide hips\" / \"athletic butt\"\n    Inference: if the description mentions \"buttocks\", \"posterior\", \"butt\", or \"ass\" without an explicit shape word, use context to pick the best shape tag. If context gives no clue, output \"round butt\".\n\nPiercings — output 1 tag per piercing explicitly mentioned anywhere on the body: \"nipple piercing\", \"belly button piercing\", \"genital piercing\", \"ear piercing\", \"nose piercing\", \"lip piercing\", \"eyebrow piercing\", or as described. Only include if the piercing is explicitly named. NEVER output tags for absent piercings. This step is ALWAYS evaluated — do not skip it based on the anatomy gate.\n\n14. Penis — up to 2 tags