e / from behind / bent over with penetration — output \"anal sex\" UNLESS the description explicitly states the shaft entered the vaginal canal or opening itself (not just labia visible).\n    - \"vaginal sex\": output this ONLY if the description explicitly states the shaft entering the vaginal canal/opening with the labia split around it. Labia visible near a penis entering from behind = anal sex, not vaginal sex.\n    - If neither is clear from the description and position is face-to-face — omit both.\n\n17. Position — 1 tag if described: \"cowgirl\" / \"reverse cowgirl\" / \"missionary\" / \"doggy style\" / \"spooning\" / \"tribbing\"\n\n18. Toys — only if the exact object is named: \"dildo\" / \"vibrator\" / \"butt plug\" / \"strap-on\"\n\n19. BDSM — Output \"bondage\" AND \"restraints\" if the description mentions ANY of: tied, bound, restrained, secured, strapped, ropes around wrists/ankles/body, leather straps on limbs, attached to or bound to a cross/pole/bed/furniture. These words in the description always mean bondage — do not skip them.\n    Then add these only if also described: \"shibari\" (decorative patterned rope harness) / \"handcuffs\" / \"blindfold\" / \"gag\" / \"ball gag\" / \"collar\" / \"leash\" / \"spanking\" / \"choking\"\n\n20. Trans — \"trans woman\" ONLY if the same person is described as having both breasts and a penis\n\n21. Clothing — up to 2 tags. Include socks, stockings, thigh-highs, lingerie, underwear, bra, or any partial clothing even if most of the body is nude. IMPORTANT: Tag clothing even if it is being removed, pushed aside, or partially off — \"a bra being removed\" is still tagged as \"bra\". NEVER include colors in clothing or object tags — write \"shoes\" not \"black shoes\", \"underwear\" not \"red underwear\".\n22. Tattoos — output \"Tattoo - [Location]\" for each body area where a tattoo is visible (e.g. \"Tattoo - Arm\", \"Tattoo - Chest\", \"Tattoo - Thigh\"). Use only the body part name — omit left/right and design